SIMPLE: intruder
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intruder
<hw>In*trud"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
intrudes; one who thrusts himself in, or enters without right, or
without leave or welcome; a trespasser.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were all strangers and <qex>intruders</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <def>A person who enters a
private residence or place of business with the intention to perform a
criminal act; <as>as, killed by an <ex>intruder</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intrudress</ent>⟦br⟧
